Subject: in_dxf: BLOCKROTATEACTION's third connection point is 96/305

The DXF writer emits conn_pts groups as dxf + vcount with vcount starting
at the field offset (dwg2.spec BlockAction_ConnectionPts), so a rotation
action's conn_pts[2] goes out as 96/305 — matching AutoCAD's own DXF. The
reader, however, expected bl_code + i - first = 94/303, so LibreDWG could
not re-read its own output (nor AutoCAD's): every real drawing carrying a
dynamic block with a rotation action failed with "Unexpected DXF code 96,
expected 94". Align the reader call with the writer.

Found by IngeCAD's round-trip fidelity harness (same hunt as #1311-#1315).

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

--- a/src/in_dxf.c
+++ b/src/in_dxf.c
@@ -8472,7 +8472,10 @@ add_AcDbBlockRotationAction (Dwg_Object *restrict obj, Bit_Chain *restrict dat)
 {
   Dwg_Data *dwg = obj->parent;
   Dxf_Pair *pair;
-  pair = add_BlockAction_ConnectionPts (obj, dat, 2, 1, 94, 303);
+  // conn_pts[2] of a rotation action is written as group 96/305 (the DXF
+  // writer emits dxf + vcount with vcount starting at 2, matching AutoCAD);
+  // expecting 94/303 here rejected every real file carrying one.
+  pair = add_BlockAction_ConnectionPts (obj, dat, 2, 1, 96, 305);
   if (pair)
     return pair;
   return NULL;
